anax
------------------------------------------
anax is an open source C++ entity system designed to be portable, lightweight
and easy to use. It is aimed toward Game Development, however it would be
possible to use it for other projects.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libanax-devel-2.1.0-1bl2
  libanax2-2.1.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.5-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/miguelmartin75/anax

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/miguelmartin75/anax/archive/refs/tags/v2.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack anax-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./anax-2.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/anax-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/anax-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libanax2-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libanax-devel-2.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(anax)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/anax.README
  /usr/share/doc/anax/CHANGELOG.md
  /usr/share/doc/anax/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/anax/README.md

(libanax2)
  /usr/bin/cyganax-2.dll

(libanax-devel)
  /usr/include/anax/Component.hpp
